questions.question:
Given the following code, what is the output?

String color = "RED";
switch (color) {
    case "red": System.out.println("lower"); break;
    case "RED": System.out.println("upper"); break;
    case "Red": System.out.println("mixed"); break;
}

What is the output of the following code?

int x = 3;
switch (x) {
    case 1: System.out.println("A");
    case 2: System.out.println("B");
    case 3: System.out.println("C");
    case 4: System.out.println("D"); break;
    case 5: System.out.println("E");
}

What is the output of the following code?

int num = 10;
switch (num) {
    default: System.out.println("Default");
    case 1: System.out.println("One"); break;
    case 2: System.out.println("Two");
}

Given the following code, what is printed?

int choice = 2;
switch (choice) {
    case 1: System.out.println("One");
    case 2: System.out.println("Two");
    case 3: System.out.println("Three");
    case 4: System.out.println("Four");
    default: System.out.println("Default");
}

What is the output of the following code?

char grade = 'B';
switch (grade) {
    case 'A': System.out.println("Excellent"); break;
    case 'B': System.out.println("Good"); break;
    case 'C': System.out.println("Satisfactory"); break;
    default: System.out.println("Invalid"); break;
}

Which of the following does this code demonstrate?

switch (month) {
    case 4: case 6: case 9: case 11:
        days = 30; break;
    case 2:
        days = 28; break;
    default:
        days = 31; break;
}

Does the following code compile?

int value = 5;
final int CONSTANT = 5;
switch (value) {
    case CONSTANT:
        System.out.println("Match");
        break;
}

What is the output of the following code?

int startStep = 3;
switch (startStep) {
    case 1: System.out.println("Step 1");
    case 2: System.out.println("Step 2");
    case 3: System.out.println("Step 3");
    case 4: System.out.println("Step 4");
    case 5: System.out.println("Step 5");
}
